<h2 id="elizabeth-myles">Elizabeth Myles</h2>

<p>Elizabeth is a graduate of <a href="http://www.lonestar.edu/tomball.htm" target="_blank">Lone Star College-Tomball</a> and the <a href="http://www.uh.edu/" target="_blank">University of Houston</a>.  Her prize-winning short fiction appeared several times 
in <a href="http://www.lonestar.edu/past-inkling-issues.htm"><em>Inkling</em></a> the Creative Arts Magazine of LSC-Tomball, and her previous novel, <a href="/novels/fear-and-laundry/"><em>Fear and Laundry</em></a>, was honored as a notable entry in the teen 
category of <a href="http://www.shelfmediagroup.com/pages/issues.html" target="_blank"><em>Shelf Unbound Magazine</em></a>‚Äôs <a href="https://issuu.com/shelfunbound/docs/shelf_unbound_december-january_2014" target="_blank">Writing Competition for Best Independently Published Book</a>. <em>Fear and Laundry</em> was
subsequently included in a special contest issue of <em>Shelf Unbound Magazine</em> spotlighting the work of ‚Äúsome of today‚Äôs best indie authors.‚Äù</p>

<p>Elizabeth and her handsome husband, <a href="https://stevemyles.site/">Steve</a>, live and run together in Texas, where Elizabeth also spends her non-writing time reading, cooking and baking, 
listening to Nine Inch Nails, and watching sci-fi and horror movies, episodes of <em>Supernatural</em>, and old DVDs of <em>The X-Files</em>.  She loves hearing from readers,
so feel free to contact her at <a href="mailto:elizabeth(at)mylesandmyles.info">elizabeth(at)mylesandmyles.info</a> and connect with her on the social networks below.</p>

